<H3><A NAME=SECTION000133100000000000000>Mosaic Behaviour</A></H3>
<P>
<A HREF="node3.html#sectHTX">HTX</A> determines whether you have an invocation of
<A NAME=tex2html61 HREF="http://www.ncsa.uiuc.edu/SDG/Software/Mosaic/NCSAMosaicHome.html "><em>Mosaic</em></A> running by looking for the <tt>.mosaicpid</tt>
file which it creates in your login directory and then checking that
the browser process it describes still exists. This means that if you
have more than one invocation of <em>Mosaic</em> running on the same
machine, HTX will normally talk to the one you started most
recently. If you run <em>Mosaic</em> on two machines that share the same
<tt>.mosaicpid</tt> file, the results can be unpredictable.
<P>
If you open new windows from within <em>Mosaic</em>, HTX output will generally
go to the most recently used one. This can sometimes make it difficult
to use more than one window to view different documents, as HTX output
tends to over-write whichever was used last. The best way of avoiding
this problem is to start two separate copies of the browser.
<P>
